column5: I finally got out for my first brook trout of the season. I felt like an alcoholic anxious for a drink, but all the tension disappeared after the first few hook-ups. All on the fly too!
Sweet Fish. I always eagerly await your post. Dry or streamer?
Absolutely beautiful! Thanks for sharing with us.
What beautiful fish ! And broad shoulders on em too !  What part of the province were you ?
Now that's what I'm talking about right there !!!!!! Wow ... Awesome ..... Cheers
Great catch!!!,that is defineatly on my list of fly fishing want to doos!!!
You live in a  great part of this province.  Real nice fish.
Fantastic fish.  I can only imagine the thrill of a catch like that on the fly.
Beauty humpback chars there Al.  Some great colors showing for early season, late ice out fish.  Looking forward to a go at 'em soon.  Had to have felt good getting out.
Nice fish. Hoping to meet a few like that on my trip up to Nipigon this year.

It was a real blast getting out and catching a few on some streamers. We have had a lot water up here this spring so the lakes and rivers are very high. Heading back there again tomorrow. Its a tough job, but somebody has to do it.
